The paper deals with algorithms for finding maximum matchings in graphs with unknown edges, which is a problem in graph theory and optimization (cs.DS). The problem involves probabilistic sets, which suggests a connection to game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents theoretical results and empirical experiments, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
